    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i noticed the bottom leaves on my tomato plants are turning kinda yellow lately. any idea what's going on or how i can fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing bottom leaves on tomatoes, especially when they're older, can be a sign of a few things, like a minor nutrient deficiency or sometimes overwatering. It's a common issue, but you'll want to check your soil moisture first, as too much water can drown the roots, which is a big problem for any plant. You can try letting the top inch or two of soil dry out between waterings; if the soil is constantly soggy, that's probably the culprit. If the soil is dry, you might need to give them a gentle drink, but make sure it soaks in properly.",
